class Solution {
    public int[] separateDigits(int[] nums) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        for (int num : nums) {
            sb.append(num);
        }
        int n = sb.length();
        int[] answer = new int[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            answer[i] = sb.charAt(i) - '0';
        }
        return answer;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n*m)
space complexity: O(n*m)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates over the input array, converting each number to a string and appending it to a StringBuilder. It then creates an output array and populates it with the individual digits. The time complexity is O(n*m) where n is the number of elements in the input array and m is the average number of digits in the numbers.
